Bulletin Issued in Syria to Mark February Holiday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- An information bulletin titled "The Greatest National Holiday of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea" was issued by Damascus University on Feb. 1 on the occasion of the February holiday.
 The bulletin said that Feb. 16, the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il, is the  greatest national holiday of the Korean people, adding that the progressive mankind of the world including the Syrian people extend the greatest glory to him and recollect with deep emotion his revolutionary exploits on the occasion of the day.
 It continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He provided the world progressives with a powerful ideological and theoretical weapon for carrying out the cause of independence against imperialism based on the scientific faith and the Songun idea. This occupies a particular place among his feats performed for the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No force on earth can break the single-minded unity of the army and the people of the DPRK around him.

School Youth and Children Vow Loyalty to Kim Jong Il
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- A national meeting of school youth and children took place in front of the old home of leader Kim Jong Il in the secret camp in Mt. Paektu on Feb. 8 on the occasion of the auspicious February holiday. At the meeting its participants vowed to accomplish generation after generation the revolutionary cause of Juche, which started in Mt. Paektu, true to the leadership of Kim Jong Il.
 Its participants laid floral baskets and bouquets before the home. Led by Ri Myong Won, secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, they pledged themselves to share the destiny with Kim Jong Il, become human bullets and bombs ready to dedicate their youth to devotedly defending the headquarters of the revolution and the young vanguard giving steady continuity to the tradition of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They resolved to bring about a more signal Songun revolutionary surge in all difficult and arduous work places to build a great prosperous powerful nation, equip themselves with the transparent anti-U.S. class consciousness and resolutely smash the imperialists' ideological and cultural poisoning and their psychological warfare with a revolutionary ideological offensive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also evinced their determination to eternally glorify President Kim Il Sung's idea of the youth movement and the exploits he performed in the movement and establish the unitary leadership system of Kim Jong Il throughout the youth league in order to develop the youth league organizations shining with the august name of the President into ones devotedly defending the leader, the revolutionary organizations strong in unity and militancy this significant year which greeted the 60th birthday of the youth league. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were officials concerned and school youth and children from across the country participating in the study tour of the old home.

National Seminar on Undying Feats of Kim Jong Il Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- A national seminar on the immortal feats performed by leader Kim Jong Il in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation with his Songun revolutionary leadership took place at the People's Palace of Culture on Feb. 8.
 Speakers at the seminar profoundly explained and proved the immortal feats Kim Jong Il performed in the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation with his energetic Songun revolutionary leadership. 
 Song Ja Rip, president of Kim Il Sung University, said that what is important in the ideological and theoretical exploits of Kim Jong Il is that he comprehensively systematized President Kim Il Sung's idea of attaching importance to arms, military affairs and provided a powerful ideological and theoretical weapon to glorify the new century as a century of victory and glory in which independence and prosperity will be achieved. And he has put the President's Songun idea overall into the present revolutionary practice, thus demonstrating the dignity of the country and the nation to the world over and opening a new turning point in socialist construction and the development of the revolution, the speaker added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hong Chang Mo, secretary of the Rodong Sinmun Primary Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, noted that it is the historical feats of Kim Jong Il that he has achieved the single-minded unity of the Party and revolutionary ranks on the highest level under the uplifted banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cha Kyong Il, president of Kim Il Sung Political University, stated that the greatness of Kim Jong Il finds its expression in the fact that he indicated the unique way of building a military power by closely combining ideology and politics with military affairs and successfully accomplished the cause of building a military power with his outstanding ability and matchless devotion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak Son Ho, president of the University of National Economies, said: Kim Jong Il carried forward and developed the basic line of socialist economic construction, set forth by Kim Il Sung, in conformity with the present realistic conditions to elucidate the line of economic construction in the era of Songun. This is the distinguished feats he performed in providing the most scientific and revolutionary theoretical and practical weapon in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation.
 Pak Yong Chol, vice-director of the National Reunification Institute, said that Kim Jong Il is the peerless patriot who ushered in the era of "By our nation itself", the June 15 era of reunification by providing the June 15 joint declaration and opened a turning phase of national reunification by mobilizing all the Koreans to a vigorous struggle for the implementation of the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending the seminar were Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the C.C., the WPK, Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education, and officials concerned, party and administration officials of national institutions and in Pyongyang city, officials of working people's organizations, officials of educational, scientific and party cadre training institutions and officials in the fields of literature and art and the press and preservation of the revolutionary historical relics.

S. Korean Military Authorities Urged to Clarify Its Stand
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The defence minister of south Korea talked about "a strong army," revealing the intention to go ahead with south Korea-U.S. joint military exercises aimed at attacking the north though the nation lives in the June 15 era of reunification.
 Minju Joson Thursday in a signed commentary terms it sophism, urging the south Korean military authorities to clarify whether they stand for reconciliation and cooperation or for confrontation and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean military authorities announced that they would stage the joint military exercises with the U.S. as scheduled at a time when the talks between the military authorities of the north and the south are on the doorstep. This is an indication that they are still regarding the north as "the principal enemy" and they are not interested in the above-said military talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dialogue and war exercises can never go together. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an unpardonable crime that a person responsible for those talks made such remarks spoiling the atmosphere of dialogue, agitating confrontation and war.
 It is as clear as noonday that if they stage such joint military exercises with the U.S. at any cost, this will only result in stoking distrust between the north and the south and escalating the tension and, furthermore, playing havoc with the results of the hard work jointly done by the north and the south.

Sulfuric Mud Widely Used in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The Pyongyang Sulfuric Mud Research Center of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has made successes in the research work for extending the application range of the sulfuric mud.
 The research team, which had kept the research within medical treatment, has succeeded in developing seed treatment agent and fodder additive to make an effective use of them in agriculture and other fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has also solved the scientific and technical issues arising in industrializing the process of sulfuric mud. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Successes have been made in manufacturing various health goods and cosmetics with sulfuric mud as raw materials. Among them are mud steam bath agent, mud poultice agent, nutritive beauty agent and health drinking water additive.
 Many countries are expressing interest in and demanding sulfuric mud protyle goods, powder and the solution produced by the center.

Korean Folklore Museum 50 Years Old
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- Fifty years have passed since the Korean Folklore Museum was founded on February 10, Juche 45 (1956).
 The museum preserves more than 30,000 historical relics and data of national treasure value belonging to the period from the Neolithic era to the end of the 19th century. They comprehensively show the folk tradition and the good manners and customs of the Korean nation such as production customs, food, clothing and housing customs, family etiquette, salutation courtesy and folk games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibits are on display, divided into seven halls in a systematic way according to times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are farming tools including 8,000 years-old horn-hoe, wooden plough, iron sickle and ax, shovel (with a rope attached to each side of the blade) and iron plough. And they include rice, foxtail millet, kaoliang, bean, millet and other grains produced 6,000 years ago, primitive earthenware and ceramics, wooden, straw, bamboo and metal handicrafts and various kinds of paper representing various eras.
 There are traditional kitchen utensils, data of famous dishes indigenous to local areas, sets of seven and twelve dishes for a table, clothes, hats and shoes according to sexes and occupations, ornaments including hairpins and finger rings and data showing the origination of floor heating system and its changes. On display there are data showing the house furnishing, education of children, wedding ceremony, first birthday party and memorial service, and a grand folding screen, models and visual aids reflecting folk amusement and games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the materials indicate excellent living customs and traditions of the Korean people.
 The museum, located in the central part of Pyongyang, is a center for the education in folklore tradition and for preserving and studying cultural remains. 
 The Korean folk relics show and similar ones have been held at the museum, demonstrating the fine culture and folk tradition of the nation within and without.
 An Sun Chol, curator of the museum, told KCNA it has been visited by over 4 million working people, youth students and schoolchildren and some 50,000 overseas Koreans and foreigners.

DPRK-Japan Inter-governmental Talks Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- The DPRK-Japan inter-governmental talks for the normalization of their relations took place in Beijing from Feb. 4 to 8, 2006.
 The talks discussed the issue of Japan's redemption of its past and security and abduction issues to implement the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration adopted on September 17, 2002 and other issues of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the issue of Japan's redemption of its past, the DPRK side clarified its stand that Japan should conduct economic cooperation with the DPRK as stipulated in the declaration, to begin with, and that it should pay for the hideous crimes perpetrated against humanity such as forcible drafting of more than 8.4 million Koreans, massacre of more than one million of them and its taking away 200,000 Korean women as "comfort women" for the Imperial Japanese Army as a separate issue from the economic cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As regards the status of the Koreans in Japan, one of the issues to be settled for Japan's redemption of its past, the DPRK side recalled the background against which the Koreans were forced to settle in Japan and their present conditions and requested the Japanese side to stop the suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan and the discrimination against the Koreans in Japan, guarantee them national education and promote it, enforce socio-economic policies for them and protect their economic activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Turning to the issue of cultural treasures, the DPRK side reiterated its stand that Japan should unconditionally return all the cultural treasures it looted in Korea during its occupation of Korea on the principle of returning treasures to the places of their origin, restore the devastated cultural treasures to their former glory and compensate for those treasures which were so severely vandalized that it is hard to return and restore. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Concerning the security issue, the DPRK side pointed out that its missile launch is an issue pertaining to its sovereignty from a to z and urged Japan to refrain from conducting such acts that may spark off serious concern about regional peace and stability as the enactment of a war law, the retrogressive revision of the constitution, nuclear weaponization and space militarization through the launch of spy satellites.
 As regards the abduction issue, the DPRK side reiterated the sincere efforts it has exerted for the settlement of this issue so far and its stand toward the issue and pointed to the injustice of the Japanese side's new assertions about the "repatriation of survivors", "probe into the truth" and "extradition of criminals," etc.
 It also strongly demanded Japan extradite the Japanese criminals who had lured and abducted DPRK citizens in recent years.

DPRK Foreign Ministry Spokesman Urges U.S. to Make Policy Switchover
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 9 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry gave the following answer to a question raised by KCNA today in connection with the fact that the United States is attempting to shift the responsibility for the stalled six-party talks on to the DPRK while persistently misleading the public opinion over the issue of financial sanctions against it:
ï¿½@Officials of the U.S. State Department were reported to have recently repeated their absurd assertions that the financial sanctions are a separate issue from the six-party talks and it is a measure to defend the interests and currency of the U.S.
 We do not care about their efforts to protect their own state interests and currency.
 What merits our serious attention is that they abuse it for defaming the political system in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The results of the past several months' investigation clearly proved that there is no evidence proving the DPRK's issue of counterfeit notes or money laundering.
 Nevertheless, the U.S. is applying unreasonable financial sanctions against it on the basis of sheer fabrications. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the U.S. to respect the state sovereignty of the DPRK and opt for peaceful co-existence is the key to the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula.
 The DPRK, which has long survived the U.S. sanctions, attaches so much importance to the lift of the financial sanctions because it is a touchstone showing whether Washington is  willing to make a switchover in its policy or not.
 A peaceful negotiated settlement of the nuclear issue can never be possible without the U.S. switchover in its policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Clear is the U.S. aim. That is to label the DPRK an "illegal state," tarnish its prestige and image, isolate and blockade it internationally and thus force it to abandon its nuclear program first. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This diametrically runs counter to the September 19, 2005 joint statement adopted at the six-party talks and lays a stumbling block in the way of denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is self-evident that no matter how frequently we sit at the negotiating table with such partner it is hard to expect any substantial results. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent policy of the DPRK government to oppose all sorts of illegal acts in the financial field. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has perfect legal and institutional mechanisms to combat such illegal acts as counterfeiting notes and money laundering and any illegal acts are liable to severe punishment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will as ever actively join the international actions against money laundering. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Invariable is its basic stand to attain the goal of denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula, implement the joint statement adopted at the six-party talks and seek a negotiated peaceful settlement of the issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The point at issue is the U.S. attitude. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. must be fully aware of what it should do.
